    "description": "An air-powered rifle, firing a heavy 13mm round shot at&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">180m/second. The rifle is smoothbore to reduce barrel friction, and has a detachable air&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">reservoir for 20 shots. It can be manually recharged (taking 15 mins). The weapon has&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">an integral tubular magazine. Useful on low-tech colonies, since lead ammunition can&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">be quickly and easily handmade. Comes with 500g air pump and 250g bullet-casting kit.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">Example: Pritchard or Giradoni Air Gun.</span>",
